This paper proposes a novel framework for training GANs based on distance metric learning. The paper focuses on improving the stability of training GANs, which is a common problem in the field of machine learning. The proposed approach is evaluated on several representative datasets, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and multimedia (cs.MM).
